article.headline: Fairfield 63, Loyola, Md. 60
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Yorel Hawkins scored 10 points and had 17 rebounds and Fairfield survived a second-half surge by Loyola of Maryland in a 63-60 victory on Friday night. Greg Nero added 15 points and Anthony Johnson and Jonathan Han each scored 14 for the Stags (10-6, 3-2 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), who have won 11 consecutive games at Reitz Arena. Brett Harvey scored 21 points and Jamal Barney added 19 for the Greyhounds (5-11, 1-4), who were playing their first home game in 30 days. Barney?s dunk with 8:23 remaining capped an 18-6 run and gave Loyola its first lead, 51-50, since midway through the first half. A 3-pointer by Harvey on the next possession made the score 54-50, but the Greyhounds were held to one field goal -- on a goaltending -- the rest of the way. Nero and Hawkins each made two free throws in the final 45.7 seconds to seal the victory.
